You are working on God Clause — an embeddable AI governance framework for TypeScript/Node.js.

## Core Concept
YAML trust contracts define rules. A three-valued policy engine evaluates them: permit, deny, or MODIFY (attach obligations like PII redaction). This is different from OPA's binary allow/deny.

## Quick Reference
- Entry point: `src/governance.ts` (GodClause class)
- All types: `src/types.ts` (~200 types, single source of truth)
- All exports: `src/index.ts` (if it's not here, it's not public)
- Tests: `tests/{module}.test.ts`, vitest, 504 tests
- Node >= 20, TypeScript strict, CommonJS, 4 deps (ajv, commander, uuid, yaml)

## Architecture
- `src/engine/` — Policy engine, evaluator, MCP router, compiled evaluator, rate limiting
- `src/contracts/` — Parser, schema, registry, watcher, signed bundles
- `src/audit/` — SHA-256 hash chain, Merkle seals, proof bundles, immutable sink
- `src/middleware/` — HTTP, LangChain/Vercel AI hooks, streaming PII interceptor
- `src/server/server.ts` — REST API (24 endpoints + SSE)
- `src/attestation/` — IETF RATS RFC 9334, trust anchors (software/TPM/SGX stubs)
- `src/sandbox/` — WASM + V8 isolate sandboxes
- `src/crypto/` — DSSE signing, RFC 3161 timestamps
- `src/compliance/` — TLA+ formal verification, 6 compliance frameworks
- `examples/` — OpenAI/Claude/Gemini wrappers, MCP demo, 9 threat contracts

## Rules
1. ALL types go in `src/types.ts` — never define types inline
2. ALL public exports go through `src/index.ts`
3. NO new npm dependencies — use Node.js built-ins (crypto, vm, WebAssembly, fs)
4. NO `new Function()` or `eval()` — use closure composition
5. NO `any` in source files — TypeScript strict mode, zero type errors
6. Audit sinks implement `AuditSink` interface from `src/audit/audit-log.ts`
7. Trust contracts require: schema_version, metadata, data_governance, rules
8. Run `npx tsc --noEmit && npx vitest run` to verify changes
9. Run `npm run format` before committing

## Common Patterns
- PolicyDecision has three outcomes: "permit" | "deny" | "modify"
- "modify" carries obligations: `{ type: "redact_pii", params: { replacement: "[REDACTED]" } }`
- MCP Router is fail-closed: unmatched tools are denied by default
- Contract YAML validated by AJV schema at `src/contracts/schema.ts`
- Examples use simulated LLM calls (no real API keys needed)
